1. The URL scheme blocklist regex `^(?:\w+script|data):` is interesting - it blocks `\w+script` (like `javascript`) and `data:` but uses `\w+` which requires word characters. This might miss things like `vbscript:`.
2. The regex `^data-[\-\w.]` for data attributes seems to be missing the `+` quantifier and the `$` anchor (compare: `^aria-[-\w]+$` has proper quantifiers).
